results.name: Expansion of eta(q)/eta(q^5)^5 in powers of q.
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = -1..10000
W. Duke, Continued fractions and modular functions, Bull. Amer. Math. Soc. 42 (2005), 137-162. See page 150.
formula: G.f. A(x) satisfies: 0=f(A(x), A(x^2), A(x^4)) where f(u, v, w)=u^2*w^2 +2*u*v^2*w +4*u*v^3 -v^3*w.
mathematica: QP:= QPochhammer; Table[SeriesCoefficient[QP[q]/QP[q^5]^5, {q, 0, n}], {n, 0, 50}] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Dec 13 2017 *)
program: (PARI) {a(n)=local(A); if(n<-1, 0, n++; A=x*O(x^n); polcoeff( eta(x+A)/eta(x^5+A)^5, n))}
